  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Cut the plywood",
      "body": "Cut a 17\" wide strip of 3/4\" thick plywood.\nCut the seat, back, and two support braces.\nDraw and cut two of each leg type with a jigsaw.\nDrill pocket holes in the pieces according to the graphic here.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/cb8953018eb4cde9.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Assemble",
      "body": "Use the pocket holes to attach the Seat and back to leg type 1.\nGlue leg type 2 to inside of leg type 1.\nScrew leg type 2 to seat.\nScrew the braces in between legs.\n\n**Tip:** Note - you could blow up this drawing for a template, if desired.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/526dda6498f021b3.webp"
    }
